cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.CY, cs.NI, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the application of game theory and ICT concepts in solving challenges in demand side management in the smart grid. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also involves the use of distributed algorithms, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the mathematical formulation of the problem, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry and Topology). The use of smart meters and appliance scheduling involves the use of networked systems, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms to find solutions, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
